ZH: 请小声点，不要吵到别人。
EN: Please speak quietly, don't disturb others.

ZH: 她小声地问道：“这是哪里？”
EN: She whispered quietly, "Where are we?".

ZH: 小声点，孩子们正在睡觉。
EN: Keep it down, the kids are sleeping.

ZH: 当心小声说话，不要惊动动物。
EN: Be careful, speak softly, don't startle the animals.

ZH: 奶奶小声地告诉我她的秘密。
EN: My grandma quietly told me her secret.

ZH: 我们小声商量了一下该如何解决这个问题。
EN: We whispered to each other quietly on how to solve this problem.

ZH: 请小声一点，不要在图书馆大声说话。
EN: Please be quiet, don't speak loudly in the library.

ZH: 他小声地对我说：“我爱你”。
EN: He whispered softly to me, "I love you".

ZH: 小心小声讨论悄悄话。
EN: Carefully speak softly when discussing secrets.

ZH: 他们小声交谈，不想被别人听到。
EN: They whispered quietly, not wanting anyone else to hear.

ZH: 我小声地问她的名字，不想引起注意。
EN: I quietly asked for her name, not wanting to draw attention.

ZH: 请小声说话，不要吵醒了孩子。
EN: Speak softly, don't wake the child up.

ZH: 在这个静谧的夜晚，我们只能小声讲话。
EN: On this quiet night, we can only speak softly.

ZH: 他们在黑暗中小声交谈，不想被发现。
EN: They whispered quietly in the darkness, not wanting to be found out.

ZH: 我们小声议论他的行为，却并没有勇气面对他。
EN: We quietly discussed his behavior, but didn't have the courage to confront him.

ZH: 请小声点，我正在专心工作。
EN: Please keep it down, I'm focusing on my work.

